question:
District category contains Jewelry District, Government Complex, and Ancient City.
Supermarkets category contains Trader Joe's, Food Lion, and Piggly Wiggly.
The number of each Jewelry District 's Trader Joe's equals 13.
The number of each Ancient City 's Food Lion equals 11 more than each Jewelry District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Government Complex 's Food Lion equals 10 times each Jewelry District 's Trader Joe's.
How many Supermarkets does Ancient City have?
solution:
Define each Jewelry District 's Trader Joe's as t; So t = 13.
Define each Jewelry District 's Supermarkets as q; So q = t = 13.
Define each Ancient City 's Food Lion as G; So G = 11 + q = 11 + 13 = 1.
Define each Ancient City 's Supermarkets as o; So o = G = 1.
